#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn47.37"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.37:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.37:0.2"
msgid "4. Ananussutavagga "
msgstr "4. Not Learned From Anyone Else "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.37:0.3"
msgid "37. Chandasutta "
msgstr "37. Desire "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn47.37:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, satipaṭṭhānā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of mindfulness meditation. "

msgctxt "sn47.37:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn47.37:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.37:1.4"
msgid "Tassa kāye kāyānupassino viharato yo kāyasmiṃ chando so pahīyati. "
msgstr "As they do so they give up desire for the body. "

msgctxt "sn47.37:1.5"
msgid "Chandassa pahānā amataṃ sacchikataṃ hoti. "
msgstr "When desire is given up they realize the deathless. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn47.37:2.1"
msgid "Vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.37:2.2"
msgid "Tassa vedanāsu vedanānupassino viharato yo vedanāsu chando so pahīyati. "
msgstr "As they do so they give up desire for feelings. "

msgctxt "sn47.37:2.3"
msgid "Chandassa pahānā amataṃ sacchikataṃ hoti. "
msgstr "When desire is given up they realize the deathless. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.182, sc3
msgctxt "sn47.37:3.1"
msgid "Citte cittānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of the mind—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.37:3.2"
msgid "Tassa citte cittānupassino viharato yo cittamhi chando so pahīyati. "
msgstr "As they do so they give up desire for the mind. "

msgctxt "sn47.37:3.3"
msgid "Chandassa pahānā amataṃ sacchikataṃ hoti. "
msgstr "When desire is given up they realize the deathless. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn47.37:4.1"
msgid "Dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.37:4.2"
msgid "Tassa dhammesu dhammānupassino viharato yo dhammesu chando so pahīyati. "
msgstr "As they do so they give up desire for principles. "

msgctxt "sn47.37:4.3"
msgid "Chandassa pahānā amataṃ sacchikataṃ hotī”ti. "
msgstr "When desire is given up they realize the deathless.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.37:4.4"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
